WEBVTT

00:19.770 --> 00:21.101
(GASPS)

00:23.232 --> 00:24.312
(GASPS)

00:29.197 --> 00:31.813
(SPEAKING THAI)

00:57.892 --> 00:59.723
I'm turning into wood.

01:12.990 --> 01:14.241
(SIGHS)

01:17.245 --> 01:20.362
Breakfast in bed? Seriously?

01:22.124 --> 01:24.035
What happened has been
really hard on Mary Margaret.

01:24.126 --> 01:25.707
The least we can do is
make sure she's eating.

01:25.795 --> 01:28.161
I think it's time to give the hot cocoa
and the foot massages a rest.

01:28.256 --> 01:30.497
It's time to haul her ass out of bed
and get her to move past this.

01:31.300 --> 01:34.383
That's a little harsh, don't you think?
She took Cora's life.

01:35.137 --> 01:36.263
Is everything okay?

01:36.347 --> 01:39.714
Everything's fine, kid.
Get your coat, we're gonna be late.

01:39.809 --> 01:40.889
Bye, Gramps.

01:40.977 --> 01:42.763
I know you think
that she needs our help.

01:42.853 --> 01:45.720
But at the end of the day,
she's the only one who can help herself.

01:52.196 --> 01:53.811
MARY: Good morning.

01:55.616 --> 01:57.902
Hey. Morning.

01:58.577 --> 02:00.033
I made you some eggs.

02:00.121 --> 02:02.578
But if you're craving something else,
we can go to Granny's.

02:03.499 --> 02:05.114
Unless you have other plans?

02:05.209 --> 02:06.949
I thought I'd head out
to the woods, actually.

02:07.044 --> 02:08.079
I need to think things through.

02:08.212 --> 02:09.292
Let me come with you.

02:09.380 --> 02:11.416
David, I need to do this alone.

02:13.718 --> 02:15.583
And you have things to do.

02:15.720 --> 02:17.802
I know you've been looking fon/vard
to working in the bean fields.

02:17.888 --> 02:20.425
Yeah. Yeah, Anton says
we might have a crop soon.

02:20.558 --> 02:22.719
And once we do, we can go home.

02:22.810 --> 02:25.802
And none of what happened will matter.
It will all be in the past.

02:25.938 --> 02:28.429
| used Regina to kill her own mother.

02:29.775 --> 02:31.515
I don't think going back will erase that.

02:31.610 --> 02:33.441
-Mary Margaret...
-Please.

02:35.406 --> 02:38.068
Give me time.

02:42.663 --> 02:43.948
Hey, buddy.

02:46.167 --> 02:48.203
-How are you?
-l'm good. I brought this.

02:48.669 --> 02:51.832
I thought you could tell me what it was
really like over there.

02:51.922 --> 02:53.173
Sounds great.

02:53.257 --> 02:57.045
I tell you what,
why don't you run into the diner,

02:57.178 --> 03:00.261
get us three hot cocoas
and we'll dive in.

03:00.389 --> 03:01.549
I'm gonna have to take
a rain check on that.

03:01.640 --> 03:03.471
I need to get down to the station
to take care of some things.

03:03.601 --> 03:06.764
Can it wait? There's a couple of things
I wanna talk to you about.

03:07.772 --> 03:10.263
Tamara went to my place
to get some of her stuff.

03:10.399 --> 03:12.014
Okay...

03:12.109 --> 03:16.068
Well, her bags were in
the storage room, but Hook wasn't.

03:16.197 --> 03:17.232
Lucky.

03:17.490 --> 03:19.481
Yeah, but now he's out there.

03:19.617 --> 03:22.279
I'm not sure how much more trouble
he can cause anyway.

03:22.411 --> 03:25.073
The second thing
I wanna talk to you about is,

03:25.206 --> 03:28.790
the reason Tamara was getting her stuff
is that she's on her way here.

03:28.876 --> 03:30.867
Here? As in Storybrooke?

03:30.961 --> 03:32.997
Yeah. She should be here at Granny's
any minute now.

03:33.089 --> 03:34.078
What are you thinking?

03:34.215 --> 03:35.250
What do you mean?

03:35.383 --> 03:37.874
I mean, what are you gonna tell her
when she sees a giant or a werewolf

03:37.968 --> 03:39.469
run past her down Main Street?

03:39.637 --> 03:41.628
Between Greg Mendell,
our food-obsessed tourist,

03:41.722 --> 03:44.179
and now your fiancee,
this town is turning into a theme park.

03:44.266 --> 03:45.551
Maybe I didn't think it
all the way through.

03:45.643 --> 03:47.725
I'm sorry. ljust... I need her.

03:50.314 --> 03:52.054
I'm sorry, I didn't mean it to...

03:52.149 --> 03:54.686
You don't need to apologize to me.
I'm not the one you're lying to.

03:54.777 --> 03:55.812
Who's lying?

03:55.903 --> 03:59.270
Does she know who you really are
and where you're really from?

04:00.449 --> 04:03.316
Take my advice,
don't let her find out on her own.

04:03.494 --> 04:06.110
Tell her the truth. Tell her everything.

04:06.330 --> 04:08.070
(CELL PHONE CHIMES)

04:10.334 --> 04:12.325
That's her. She's 10 minutes away.

04:12.503 --> 04:14.710
Why don't you stay
and get to know her?

04:14.797 --> 04:16.412
I really should be going.

04:16.507 --> 04:18.338
I know, but we're all connected.

04:18.467 --> 04:19.877
Now, it might be nice for you two to talk.

04:20.511 --> 04:22.843
Just stay and say hello.

04:23.722 --> 04:24.848
She's bringing bagels.

04:26.725 --> 04:27.885
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

04:36.861 --> 04:38.601
(MUSIC CONTINUES PLAYING
OVER HEADPHONES)

04:38.696 --> 04:40.937
-(TW|G SNAPPING)
-(FAST-PACED FOOTSTEPS)

05:14.607 --> 05:16.518
Anyone in here?

05:16.609 --> 05:17.940
MAN: Just me.

05:29.872 --> 05:31.237
August?

05:39.423 --> 05:40.959
(SIREN WAlLlNG)

05:41.800 --> 05:43.756
-(WOMAN COUGHING)
-(BABY CRYING)

05:49.600 --> 05:50.635
August W. Booth?

05:53.395 --> 05:54.555
(CHUCKLES)

05:57.608 --> 05:58.768
I don't see anything.

06:00.110 --> 06:01.566
My leg is turning into wood.

06:01.654 --> 06:02.734
I think you should go.

06:02.821 --> 06:04.686
Wait, wait. Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

06:05.783 --> 06:06.818
l'll prove it to you.

06:09.995 --> 06:11.496
No! Stop! (YELLS)

06:13.249 --> 06:14.455
(SPEAKING CANTONESE)

06:20.130 --> 06:21.666
DOCTOR: Wait! Get back here!

06:24.260 --> 06:25.625
Hey! Get back!

06:37.856 --> 06:38.936
Who are you?

06:39.024 --> 06:40.230
Someone who can help.

06:40.317 --> 06:42.649
I heard you yelling about your situation.

06:43.529 --> 06:45.315
And I work with a man who fixes
those kinds of problems.

06:45.447 --> 06:47.904
-What kind of problems?
-The kind most people just dismiss.

06:47.992 --> 06:49.573
For the right price,
he can cure anything.

06:49.660 --> 06:50.945
(MEN TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

06:52.830 --> 06:53.990
Who is he?

06:54.123 --> 06:55.863
They call him The Dragon.

06:57.751 --> 07:00.037
MARY: But the curse broke.

07:00.170 --> 07:04.413
Not for me.
When it lifted, I could move again.

07:04.508 --> 07:06.339
But I stayed like this.

07:09.305 --> 07:13.719
This is my own punishment.
Not the Queen's. I did this to myself.

07:13.851 --> 07:15.011
August, I'm so sorry.

07:17.855 --> 07:19.436
But you don't have to hide.

07:19.523 --> 07:22.515
There are people in Storybrooke
who care about you.

07:23.485 --> 07:25.612
Emma, your father...

07:25.696 --> 07:28.779
How is he? My papa?

07:28.866 --> 07:30.652
He misses you.

07:30.743 --> 07:32.153
I know.

07:32.870 --> 07:35.202
But I can't let him see me like this.

07:35.539 --> 07:36.619
Or Emma.

07:36.707 --> 07:39.665
Please reconsider.
They could all use you back.

07:39.752 --> 07:41.037
There's been a lot going on.

07:41.170 --> 07:43.206
Henry's father returned.
Emma found him.

07:43.380 --> 07:46.122
Wait, Emma and Neal?

07:46.967 --> 07:48.628
They're back together again?

07:48.719 --> 07:49.834
Uh...

07:50.054 --> 07:54.548
Uh, no. Actually, he's engaged
to someone he met in New York.

07:54.642 --> 07:57.133
(SIGHS) lwas hoping...

07:57.227 --> 07:58.433
(CHUCKLES)

07:58.896 --> 08:01.854
That's my problem. Hoping.

08:02.733 --> 08:05.440
Hoping that things can still work out.

08:05.569 --> 08:10.313
Hoping that I can find redemption
for the mistakes that I've made.

08:11.533 --> 08:14.946
But maybe some things
you just don't come back from.

08:16.914 --> 08:18.996
No matter what you've done,
you deserve a second chance.

08:19.124 --> 08:21.331
That's easy for you to say.

08:21.418 --> 08:25.582
You've never had to worry
about forgiveness and redemption.

08:25.673 --> 08:28.130
You've never needed it.

08:29.677 --> 08:32.669
August, it's time to stop
feeling sorry for yourself.

08:32.763 --> 08:35.254
Come back to town with me,
we'll find Marco...

08:35.391 --> 08:37.928
You expect me to face him like this?

08:39.144 --> 08:40.429
A wood pile of failure?

08:40.562 --> 08:41.517
Don't say that!

08:41.605 --> 08:43.846
You wanna help me?

08:43.941 --> 08:45.056
Leave.

08:47.111 --> 08:49.898
And don't tell anyone you saw me.

08:58.455 --> 09:00.366
So, how did you guys meet?

09:02.292 --> 09:03.623
(NEAL CHUCKLES)

09:04.962 --> 09:06.077
Um...

09:06.630 --> 09:09.212
Well, I was super late to work,
rushing like crazy,

09:09.299 --> 09:13.212
guzzling my giant coffee, when
this guy crashed into me. (CHUCKLES)

09:14.430 --> 09:16.170
Hot coffee soaked my blouse.

09:16.640 --> 09:21.725
There was no time to change, so Neal
gave me his scarf to hide the stains.

09:21.812 --> 09:25.725
And he said I could keep it
or call him if I wanted to return it.

09:26.942 --> 09:28.057
(CHUCKLES)

09:28.152 --> 09:31.485
I decided to call and,
well, we've been together ever since.

09:32.281 --> 09:33.817
Sounds like fate.

09:35.617 --> 09:39.201
I've gotta drop Henry off with
his grandpa. Thanks for the bagel.

09:40.330 --> 09:42.070
It was nice meeting you, Tamara.

09:42.166 --> 09:43.906
-You, too.
-Here you go, man.

09:44.001 --> 09:45.491
Why don't you hold on to that?

09:45.627 --> 09:47.208
Okay.

09:48.005 --> 09:49.415
See you.

09:49.506 --> 09:50.837
HENRY: See you later.

09:51.467 --> 09:52.456
(DOOR CLOSING)

09:55.846 --> 09:58.132
Henry seems like a really great kid.

09:58.223 --> 09:59.679
Yeah.

09:59.933 --> 10:01.048
He has your spirit.

10:02.936 --> 10:04.016
You think?

10:08.484 --> 10:09.849
Yeah.

10:11.695 --> 10:13.936
There's something I need to tell you.

10:16.325 --> 10:19.158
Here's the thing, I'm not from here.

10:21.497 --> 10:24.364
I'm from a place called
the enchanted forest.

10:26.960 --> 10:29.076
I'm being serious.

10:30.088 --> 10:31.214
(EXHALES)

10:31.298 --> 10:34.040
Here. Go ahead.

10:45.312 --> 10:47.803
These are fairy tales.

10:49.191 --> 10:52.399
And they're real, all right?
They're more than real.

10:52.528 --> 10:54.894
They're history. They're my history.

10:57.032 --> 10:59.819
See this little boy? That's me.

10:59.910 --> 11:01.901
What the hell are you doing?

11:04.122 --> 11:06.158
I'm trying to be honest with you.

11:08.710 --> 11:11.702
If you wanted to be honest, you would
tell me what this is really about.

11:12.756 --> 11:14.337
Cute blonde who was just here?

11:14.424 --> 11:16.085
-Mother of your child?
-Emma?

11:16.218 --> 11:19.085
I'm not a fool, Neal. I saw the way
you two look at each other.

11:19.221 --> 11:20.586
It's not like that.

11:20.722 --> 11:22.428
I think it is.

11:22.558 --> 11:24.423
I think it's why
you wanted to hide under the table

11:24.518 --> 11:26.884
when Henry asked how we met.

11:26.979 --> 11:29.595
You didn't want her to hear the story.

11:31.108 --> 11:32.973
If you want to be with her, Neal,
you could've told me

11:33.068 --> 11:34.649
instead of making up crap
to force me away.

11:34.778 --> 11:35.893
I don't want to force you away.

11:35.988 --> 11:37.569
Here's the thing, Neal.

11:37.656 --> 11:42.696
When you're ready to be honest with
me about yourself and your feelings,

11:42.786 --> 11:44.447
then come find me.

11:46.290 --> 11:48.451
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

11:58.427 --> 12:00.133
We're almost there.

12:13.734 --> 12:16.146
Wait here, it shouldn't be long.

12:26.830 --> 12:29.162
You. Come. He's ready.

12:32.336 --> 12:35.203
Miss. You dropped this.

12:42.638 --> 12:43.878
Thank you.

12:48.226 --> 12:51.309
I hope you enjoy your pie. It's on me.

12:52.397 --> 12:55.434
l'm Regina Mills, mayor of Storybrooke.

12:55.901 --> 12:57.812
I'm also Henry's mother.

12:57.903 --> 13:01.191
Oh, he's the cute little kid that was
wandering through the woods, right?

13:01.281 --> 13:04.944
Yes. | just wanted to thank you
for calling me about him.

13:05.035 --> 13:09.699
Yeah, no, no sweat. l have a soft spot
for little kids in trouble.

13:11.333 --> 13:16.453
I'm fairly certain we haven't met before,
but you do seem oddly familiar.

13:16.546 --> 13:17.922
I don't see how that's possible unless...

13:19.049 --> 13:22.086
Have you spent a lot of time
in Carlisle, Pennsylvania?

13:22.219 --> 13:24.255
(LAUGHS) No, I can't say that l have.

13:25.889 --> 13:28.505
Well, if there's anything
you need during your stay here,

13:29.601 --> 13:31.262
please don't hesitate to ask.

13:36.733 --> 13:39.190
If I were you, I'd try the fish special.

13:39.277 --> 13:42.735
It's right up your alley. Blackened sole.

13:45.492 --> 13:48.734
Hey. What's up?
Why the urgent phone call?

13:48.912 --> 13:50.994
lt's August. I found him.

13:51.081 --> 13:52.617
My boy? He's alive?

13:52.708 --> 13:55.666
Yes, but he's completely wooden.

13:56.086 --> 13:58.748
He's been living in an abandoned
trailer, down near the Toll Bridge.

13:58.922 --> 14:00.128
What can we do? Can we help him?

14:01.633 --> 14:04.545
No. But I know someone
who might be able to. Mother Superior.

14:04.636 --> 14:07.378
Yes, yes. The Blue Fairy.
She helped once.

14:07.472 --> 14:10.259
She can help again. She must.

14:22.696 --> 14:23.776
He said to send you in.

14:25.949 --> 14:26.984
Good luck.

14:30.871 --> 14:32.111
(DOOR OPENING)

14:33.457 --> 14:34.663
(DOOR CLOSING)

14:45.010 --> 14:46.295
Please. Sit.

14:54.519 --> 14:57.101
Tell me, why have you come?

15:03.820 --> 15:05.321
You see that?

15:05.405 --> 15:08.568
No. Because the problem
is with your other leg.

15:09.826 --> 15:11.032
(CHUCKLES)

15:16.208 --> 15:20.417
You're turning to wood, Pinocchio.

15:22.547 --> 15:23.832
How in the hell do you know my name?

15:24.841 --> 15:27.298
Who are you? Are you from my land?

15:27.385 --> 15:32.004
August, you are in pain. Waste your
energy not on me but on your affliction.

15:32.140 --> 15:34.756
All you need to worry about
is whether I can help you.

15:34.851 --> 15:37.843
And the answer is, indeed I can.

15:37.938 --> 15:39.178
(SIGHS) Thank God.

15:40.273 --> 15:42.264
There are, however, conditions.

15:42.359 --> 15:43.439
Yeah.

15:43.985 --> 15:46.237
I need an item of great value to you.

15:46.363 --> 15:47.398
Money? I have some...

15:47.531 --> 15:49.692
No. That comes later.

15:49.783 --> 15:52.695
I need something close to your heart.

15:52.786 --> 15:55.198
Something that cannot be replaced.

16:05.382 --> 16:09.375
This? lt's worthless.

16:09.469 --> 16:11.710
The pendant, perhaps. But the string?

16:11.805 --> 16:15.218
It was the string your father used
to animate you

16:15.809 --> 16:17.800
as a freshly carved puppet.

16:19.062 --> 16:21.724
In a way, it first gave you life.

16:21.815 --> 16:25.808
It will serve as payment from your soul.

16:26.987 --> 16:28.067
Will it work?

16:28.822 --> 16:30.187
Perhaps.

16:41.084 --> 16:45.123
Now, as any vendor from this world,
I also need payment from your wallet.

16:47.591 --> 16:49.502
Ten thousand American dollars.

16:50.093 --> 16:51.253
Ten thousand?

16:52.262 --> 16:56.426
Bring the money tonight and
you shall never turn to wood again.

17:03.315 --> 17:04.930
I know about August.

17:05.025 --> 17:06.936
He came to me
shortly after the curse broke

17:07.027 --> 17:08.938
and asked if I would return him
to what he was.

17:09.029 --> 17:10.565
Why didn't you?

17:10.655 --> 17:13.112
Because what he was is what he is.

17:14.034 --> 17:17.197
Do you remember the morning I found
you on that beach all those years ago?

17:17.287 --> 17:19.369
The day I turned your son
into a real boy?

17:19.456 --> 17:22.448
Yes. It was the happiest day of my life.

17:22.542 --> 17:26.956
I told Pinocchio so long as he remained
brave, truthful and unselfish,

17:27.047 --> 17:28.708
he would stay a real boy.

17:29.424 --> 17:31.665
But I'm afraid he did not.

17:33.303 --> 17:35.134
That is why he changed back.

17:35.263 --> 17:37.094
And that's why
there's nothing I can do for him.

17:37.224 --> 17:39.010
It's true he's done
some things he regrets,

17:39.100 --> 17:40.681
we all have.

17:40.769 --> 17:42.680
But shouldn't he have another chance?

17:43.355 --> 17:45.562
If there is still a path of redemption
for August,

17:45.649 --> 17:48.140
it is one that he must travel on his own.

17:48.276 --> 17:51.484
No one can force him
or it will not be true.

17:53.365 --> 17:55.071
Don't despair, Marco.

17:55.158 --> 17:58.025
I know there's still hope for your son.

17:58.119 --> 17:59.780
There has to be.

17:59.871 --> 18:01.327
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

18:09.506 --> 18:11.042
WOMAN: Hey.

18:14.928 --> 18:16.464
Hey.

18:17.472 --> 18:19.588
You look like you could use a drink.

18:19.683 --> 18:22.550
Yeah, well,
I wasn't planning on staying very long.

18:22.686 --> 18:25.894
Come on, humor me.
Celebrating alone is no fun.

18:26.606 --> 18:27.812
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

18:38.285 --> 18:40.116
Figured a medicine man
wouldn't take plastic.

18:43.206 --> 18:44.195
Um...

18:44.791 --> 18:45.826
To second chances.

18:48.211 --> 18:50.327
Who knew they'd be so expensive.

18:56.136 --> 18:57.421
So what brought you to him?

18:57.971 --> 18:59.006
Cancer.

18:59.222 --> 19:01.429
-(S|GHS)
-Very rare form.

19:01.558 --> 19:05.392
When I was diagnosed, the specialist
told me lwas on borrowed time.

19:07.439 --> 19:10.181
Ever since, I've been all over the world
trying to find a cure.

19:10.317 --> 19:13.559
Doctors, healers. You name it.
Anyone who could promise a miracle.

19:14.988 --> 19:16.649
And no one could.

19:18.241 --> 19:19.742
And then,

19:20.035 --> 19:21.741
then I heard about The Dragon.

19:23.204 --> 19:24.239
(WINCES)

19:28.043 --> 19:29.249
How about you?

19:32.464 --> 19:34.250
-Skin condition.
-Acne? (CHUCKLES)

19:34.758 --> 19:35.747
Yeah.

19:35.842 --> 19:37.173
You know, there are creams.

19:37.260 --> 19:42.425
I wish. Now, this condition,
once it spreads, I'm done for.

19:42.557 --> 19:44.548
Well, I'm glad you found him, too.

19:44.642 --> 19:46.052
Thanks.

19:47.937 --> 19:49.598
He tell you he needed a personal item?

19:50.273 --> 19:53.185
Who carries something like that
around with them anyway?

19:54.903 --> 19:58.566
Luckily, I had a photo of
my grandmother and me in my wallet.

19:59.240 --> 20:03.574
Now, it's gone. But if my cancer is, too...

20:06.164 --> 20:07.825
(CELL PHONE CHIMING)

20:10.377 --> 20:11.366
Oh.

20:11.461 --> 20:12.917
Sorry. I'll be right back.
Will you watch this?

20:13.004 --> 20:14.710
Yeah.

20:45.036 --> 20:46.901
-(EXHALES)
-(KNOCK|NG ON DOOR)

20:47.664 --> 20:49.655
I told you to leave me alone!

20:53.044 --> 20:56.252
Hey. Long time.

21:00.677 --> 21:02.338
(PANTING)

21:06.224 --> 21:08.761
For someone who's spent
his entire life running,

21:08.852 --> 21:10.934
you should be in better shape.

21:12.689 --> 21:14.680
Well, IwiII be.

21:15.692 --> 21:17.728
You have what you promised?

21:25.869 --> 21:27.985
I believe we discussed a price.

21:28.288 --> 21:30.995
The money? Do you have it?

21:33.877 --> 21:34.992
(SIGHS)

21:36.921 --> 21:37.910
(SOBS)

21:44.220 --> 21:47.553
The body has a strange way
of sending us signals, doesn't it?

21:48.892 --> 21:51.258
The tricky part isn't hearing them,

21:51.895 --> 21:54.011
but knowing what they truly mean.

21:55.273 --> 21:57.559
Are you sure this can cure me?

21:57.692 --> 22:01.480
What's in this bottle will stop you
from turning to wood, yes.

22:01.571 --> 22:03.402
But that's just a symptom.

22:03.907 --> 22:06.899
Only you can cure yourself.

22:25.094 --> 22:26.254
(GROANS)

22:32.060 --> 22:33.095
TAMARA: Stop!

22:35.855 --> 22:36.844
That's mine.

22:37.649 --> 22:39.059
I'm so sorry.

22:40.318 --> 22:42.809
TAMARA: Hey! Somebody stop him!

22:44.614 --> 22:46.525
Out of the way!

22:49.577 --> 22:50.657
(GRUNTING)

22:54.165 --> 22:55.666
(SCREAMING)

22:59.671 --> 23:03.459
Whatever it is you have,
you deserve your fate.

23:09.764 --> 23:10.970
(SOBBING)

23:23.987 --> 23:25.568
Not much of a decorator.

23:28.074 --> 23:32.067
Then again, I guess a man
made of wood doesn't require much.

23:32.161 --> 23:34.573
You can see me? You believe?

23:34.664 --> 23:38.282
Do you think I would have chased down
someone called The Dragon if I didn't?

23:38.376 --> 23:39.991
I don't understand.

23:40.086 --> 23:43.328
What are you doing in Storybrooke?
How is this even possible?

23:43.423 --> 23:45.334
What I'm doing in Storybrooke
doesn't concern you.

23:45.425 --> 23:47.507
But I need you to do something.

23:47.594 --> 23:51.132
And after what you pulled
in Hong Kong, you owe me.

23:53.224 --> 23:54.805
What could I ever do for you?

23:54.892 --> 23:56.507
Leave.

23:57.228 --> 24:00.391
It's a simple request,
considering what I'm about to offer you.

24:05.903 --> 24:09.361
No. You're going to explain this.

24:09.490 --> 24:11.446
Did you follow me?

24:11.534 --> 24:12.865
Are you like me?

24:13.453 --> 24:17.116
Magical? No. I'm quite human.

24:17.624 --> 24:19.740
But forget for a second
why I'm here and who I am.

24:19.876 --> 24:23.539
And instead, ask yourself
the more important question. How?

24:24.213 --> 24:26.340
My cancer was
a death sentence, remember?

24:26.424 --> 24:28.836
Yet, here I am.

24:28.926 --> 24:32.544
The Dragon.
The liquid in the bottle, it worked.

24:32.639 --> 24:37.429
lt cured me, August.
And it can cure you, too.

24:37.560 --> 24:39.721
I still have some of it left.

24:40.938 --> 24:43.771
The bottle's in my apartment
in New York.

24:43.900 --> 24:45.390
You can go get it.

24:46.069 --> 24:49.277
All I ask is that
you leave Storybrooke now

24:50.490 --> 24:52.071
and never return.

24:56.412 --> 24:59.700
Neal. You're the fiancee.

24:59.791 --> 25:00.997
(SCOFFS)

25:01.584 --> 25:03.495
Are you and Neal here for the magic?

25:04.671 --> 25:08.960
Are you two trying to take
the magic from Storybrooke?

25:09.092 --> 25:12.584
Neal has nothing to do
with any of this, okay?

25:13.221 --> 25:14.461
He knows as much as you do.

25:16.933 --> 25:18.924
Actually, now you know a lot more.

25:19.811 --> 25:21.176
So do we have a deal?

25:21.270 --> 25:23.932
I can't leave without knowing
what you're doing here.

25:24.774 --> 25:25.934
Sure you can.

25:26.025 --> 25:28.016
And you will.

25:28.111 --> 25:31.274
You're the same man
I left in a Hong Kong gutter.

25:31.364 --> 25:35.198
A man willing to do anything
to save himself.

25:35.284 --> 25:37.149
And that's what I'm offering, August.

25:38.788 --> 25:40.278
Salvation.

25:46.379 --> 25:50.042
You know, I'm all set on towels,
if that's why you're here.

25:50.133 --> 25:51.339
lair dry.

25:52.135 --> 25:55.343
I'm here because I realized
why you looked so familiar to me.

25:56.389 --> 25:59.301
It's because we have met before,
haven't we?

25:59.726 --> 26:00.715
Owen.

26:03.938 --> 26:08.523
I kept this all these years
as a reminder of our time together.

26:08.651 --> 26:11.017
You were just a boy
when you gave this to me.

26:11.571 --> 26:12.981
Now look at you.

26:13.656 --> 26:14.987
All grown up.

26:18.745 --> 26:21.361
No wonder I didn't recognize you.

26:22.665 --> 26:24.326
Yeah, but I recognized you.

26:24.417 --> 26:27.659
Because you look
exactly the same, Regina.

26:27.754 --> 26:30.245
It's as if no time has passed for you.

26:30.339 --> 26:34.378
Monthlyjuice cleanse.
Does wonders for the skin.

26:34.886 --> 26:36.046
You could have come to me, Owen.

26:36.179 --> 26:38.044
You could've told me
who you were and why you're here.

26:38.181 --> 26:40.547
I think you know why I'm here.

26:40.683 --> 26:41.968
I honestly don't.

26:42.059 --> 26:43.344
I'm looking for my father.

26:43.436 --> 26:44.596
Your father?

26:45.563 --> 26:48.771
He left shortly after you did.
I never saw him again.

26:48.858 --> 26:50.849
I don't believe you.

26:51.027 --> 26:53.439
Be that as it may, it's the truth.

26:53.571 --> 26:56.438
People don'tjust disappear, Regina.

26:56.574 --> 26:59.782
Scared little boys tend to have
overactive imaginations.

26:59.869 --> 27:02.360
Well, I'm not a scared little boy
anymore, Madame Mayor.

27:02.455 --> 27:05.288
It's taken me a long time
to get back here.

27:07.043 --> 27:08.283
I'm not leaving without my father.

27:08.377 --> 27:10.117
I'm afraid you are.

27:10.213 --> 27:11.623
Because he's not here.

27:14.801 --> 27:18.714
I'll let Granny know that
you'll be checking out tomorrow.

27:19.138 --> 27:20.514
Or what?

27:20.598 --> 27:23.510
Contrary to what you might think,

27:23.601 --> 27:25.808
people can just disappear.

27:28.731 --> 27:31.222
This is all my fault.

27:31.317 --> 27:33.228
Our children make
their own decisions, Marco.

27:33.319 --> 27:35.401
You can't blame yourself
for anything that's happened.

27:35.488 --> 27:39.481
Yes, I can.
And you should blame me, too.

27:41.244 --> 27:44.077
The wardrobe I built for you,

27:44.163 --> 27:46.620
the one that transported Emma
to this world?

27:46.958 --> 27:48.744
She did not go alone.

27:48.835 --> 27:49.995
MARY: Of course she did.

27:50.086 --> 27:52.452
The wardrobe only had enough magic
to transport one person.

27:52.588 --> 27:55.125
No. That was a lie
I made the Blue Fairy tell you.

27:56.259 --> 27:59.251
It had enough magic to transport two.

27:59.929 --> 28:01.089
And it did.

28:01.681 --> 28:05.094
Your daughter and my son.

28:05.852 --> 28:06.967
Pinocchio.

28:07.103 --> 28:09.094
I could have gone with her?

28:09.188 --> 28:10.769
With Emma?

28:10.857 --> 28:15.100
There is no apology I could give
that could ever make up for what I did.

28:16.612 --> 28:17.647
But I am so sorry.

28:18.531 --> 28:19.566
EMMA: Mary Margaret!

28:19.657 --> 28:21.522
What are you doing? He's apologizing.

28:21.659 --> 28:23.365
No, no. It's okay. I deserved that.

28:23.452 --> 28:25.613
No. That wasn't me.

28:25.705 --> 28:27.320
Marco, I am so sorry.

28:27.456 --> 28:30.493
I'm not myself. You just made a mistake.

28:30.626 --> 28:32.787
I would've done
the same thing for my child.

28:34.088 --> 28:35.999
I forgive you.
You were protecting your son.

28:36.132 --> 28:41.252
No. l burdened him with a weight
no child should have to bear.

28:41.345 --> 28:42.801
And I called it love.

29:13.252 --> 29:16.494
Your photograph. It's on the desk.

29:17.340 --> 29:19.831
Do not forget to take it when you leave.

29:25.765 --> 29:29.508
Interesting choice of words from
someone who lied about being sick.

29:30.353 --> 29:32.935
You're right. I don't have cancer.

29:33.230 --> 29:34.936
And yet you sought me out.

29:35.566 --> 29:40.185
I've been searching for someone
like you for a very long time.

29:40.279 --> 29:41.359
Ah.

29:43.032 --> 29:44.397
For magic.

29:44.533 --> 29:46.444
It's rare in this world.

29:47.161 --> 29:50.870
So rare most would say it's fiction.

29:51.457 --> 29:52.697
But not you.

29:52.792 --> 29:54.248
Not me.

29:54.710 --> 29:56.416
But finding it,

29:56.545 --> 29:58.797
that has not been easy.

29:59.423 --> 30:02.085
I found the world full of frauds.

30:02.969 --> 30:04.084
Until you.

30:06.973 --> 30:08.554
l've analyzed the contents of this bottle

30:08.641 --> 30:11.223
with the most sophisticated techniques
available to man.

30:12.103 --> 30:13.968
You know what I found?

30:14.397 --> 30:15.557
Nothing.

30:15.815 --> 30:17.180
So I'm a fraud, too.

30:17.274 --> 30:18.400
No.

30:20.236 --> 30:22.568
Literally nothing.

30:22.655 --> 30:27.490
The liquid in this bottle doesn't contain
a single element found in this world.

30:29.412 --> 30:30.618
Can you explain that?

30:31.080 --> 30:32.741
What I create is not from this world,

30:32.832 --> 30:34.823
because the people who need my help

30:34.917 --> 30:38.284
suffer from afflictions
that science cannot treat.

30:40.631 --> 30:44.340
People like the man you stole that from.

30:44.427 --> 30:46.258
I didn't steal anything.

30:47.138 --> 30:49.049
I paid for what's in this bottle.

30:51.851 --> 30:53.432
But now that l have it,

30:54.103 --> 30:55.843
I can't risk anyone else finding you.

30:58.941 --> 31:00.101
(CRACKUNG)

31:00.609 --> 31:01.940
It was nice meeting you.

31:10.119 --> 31:11.655
You haven't met me.

31:13.039 --> 31:15.280
At least not the real me.

32:08.177 --> 32:12.546
(SHOUTING) Emma? Hello?
Is anyone here?

32:19.105 --> 32:20.390
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

32:21.190 --> 32:22.225
Emma Swan.

32:22.358 --> 32:24.019
Emma, it's August.

32:24.110 --> 32:25.225
-August?
-Listen to me.

32:25.361 --> 32:27.101
-l have to warn you.
-August...

32:30.199 --> 32:31.564
Warn me? Warn me about what?

32:35.371 --> 32:37.111
You disappoint me, August.

32:37.206 --> 32:39.322
I know what you did to The Dragon.

32:41.210 --> 32:42.916
A few days after you left,

32:44.046 --> 32:46.583
/ went back to beg him to ï¬x me.

32:47.383 --> 32:49.544
And we both know what / found.

32:49.635 --> 32:52.217
At the time,
/ was too wrapped up in myself

32:52.346 --> 32:54.211
to wonder what had happened.

32:54.557 --> 32:58.391
To question who could have
done such a thing.

32:59.270 --> 33:01.386
But then I found this photo in your car,

33:01.897 --> 33:02.977
and it hit me.

33:03.065 --> 33:06.432
You and your grandmother,
you went back there.

33:07.653 --> 33:08.768
You killed him.

33:08.904 --> 33:10.986
You should have left.

33:13.742 --> 33:16.199
I counted on you
to want to save yourself.

33:16.287 --> 33:18.243
Maybe that's what I'm trying to do.

33:19.582 --> 33:20.913
I've lived a life

33:21.000 --> 33:25.710
of selfishness, cowardice,
and dishonesty.

33:26.505 --> 33:28.882
And only I can cure that.

33:29.300 --> 33:32.633
Not magic. Not science. Just me.

33:34.805 --> 33:36.796
I care about the people in this town.

33:36.891 --> 33:39.098
And if you wanted
The Dragon's little bit of magic,

33:39.226 --> 33:41.217
well, you have hit the mother lode here,

33:41.312 --> 33:44.520
and you are not going
to harm anyone to get it.

33:45.107 --> 33:46.813
I'm going to warn them.

33:47.651 --> 33:48.766
No.

33:48.861 --> 33:50.101
You're not.

33:50.613 --> 33:52.444
(CRACKUNG)
(GRUNnNG)

34:02.625 --> 34:05.241
lf August is still at the station,
he's not picking up.

34:07.129 --> 34:08.118
August!

34:11.133 --> 34:12.293
(GROANS)

34:12.843 --> 34:14.299
August!

34:16.472 --> 34:17.552
My child.

34:17.640 --> 34:19.551
My boy. My boy!

34:20.851 --> 34:22.261
What happened to you?

34:22.353 --> 34:23.889
I'm so sorry, Papa.

34:24.021 --> 34:25.136
MARCO: No.

34:25.898 --> 34:27.889
There is nothing to apologize for.

34:27.983 --> 34:30.065
Everything is going to be all right.

34:33.030 --> 34:35.066
-Emma.
-August.

34:37.701 --> 34:39.282
Emma...

34:39.370 --> 34:40.655
She's...

34:49.505 --> 34:51.245
MARCO: Oh, no.

34:51.340 --> 34:52.705
Not again.

34:54.093 --> 34:55.333
(SOBBING)

34:59.098 --> 35:00.838
-August?
-No.

35:00.933 --> 35:02.548
It can't end this way.

35:02.685 --> 35:04.300
He was supposed
to get a second chance.

35:04.395 --> 35:05.384
What happened?

35:05.521 --> 35:08.763
Someone killed him to stop him
from telling us something.

35:08.857 --> 35:11.894
He used his last dying breath
to warn us.

35:11.986 --> 35:13.897
I will not let that be in vain.

35:17.866 --> 35:21.154
"Brave, truthful and unselfish."

35:21.954 --> 35:25.538
Brave, truthful and unselfish!

35:25.708 --> 35:27.619
Don't you see what this means?

35:27.710 --> 35:29.701
That's what Pinocchio
was supposed to be.

35:30.045 --> 35:32.502
There's still hope.
We need the Blue Fairy.

35:33.340 --> 35:34.625
I'm here, Henry.

35:34.717 --> 35:36.002
What does Henry mean?

35:36.093 --> 35:39.301
l was able to turn Pinocchio
into a real boy after he sacrificed

35:39.388 --> 35:41.549
his life for Marco's.

35:41.724 --> 35:45.637
If his actions today were indeed
brave, truthful and unselfish,

35:45.728 --> 35:48.390
then you're right,
there's a chance I can do it again.

35:48.897 --> 35:52.890
Please, I beg of you. Try.

36:12.212 --> 36:13.247
Father?

36:15.883 --> 36:17.248
Pinocchio?

36:21.388 --> 36:22.889
Look.

36:24.058 --> 36:25.264
Look.

36:27.102 --> 36:28.217
I'm a real boy.

36:28.645 --> 36:29.896
I'm a real boy!

36:41.283 --> 36:42.363
Honey.

36:42.451 --> 36:44.783
lt's. .. It's true.

36:47.456 --> 36:49.287
Do better this time, Pinocchio.

36:51.293 --> 36:53.784
Pinocchio? That's...

36:53.879 --> 36:54.959
Yeah.

36:56.799 --> 36:58.164
Pinocchio,

36:58.300 --> 37:00.541
l have to ask you a question.

37:00.636 --> 37:02.797
I need you to think real hard, okay?

37:03.680 --> 37:05.716
Before you turned into a little boy,

37:06.642 --> 37:08.724
you were trying to tell us
something very important.

37:08.811 --> 37:10.426
Do you remember?

37:11.855 --> 37:14.107
You were trying to warn us
about something.

37:15.442 --> 37:17.148
I don't remember.

37:18.153 --> 37:20.314
If I did, I would be truthful.

37:21.448 --> 37:22.654
I promise.

37:40.342 --> 37:45.006
If you want to head back to New York,
I wouldn't blame you.

37:45.139 --> 37:47.505
I know this isn't what you signed up for.

37:50.894 --> 37:53.852
What I signed up for is you.

37:55.732 --> 37:57.518
I love you.

37:58.360 --> 38:01.477
I can't believe how lucky I was
to have met you.

38:03.365 --> 38:04.696
We were both lucky.

38:05.909 --> 38:08.992
It must have been one hell
of a flight from Hong Kong.

38:09.496 --> 38:10.576
You've looked better.

38:10.706 --> 38:11.912
Well, I've felt better.

38:12.374 --> 38:13.910
I'm turning back to wood, Neal.

38:15.502 --> 38:17.038
Which means that
Emma's in Storybrooke.

38:17.171 --> 38:18.581
You're going there, aren't you?

38:18.714 --> 38:21.922
I gotta get her to break the curse
to stop what's happening to me.

38:22.009 --> 38:24.591
If she breaks the curse,
my father is gonna remember who he is

38:24.720 --> 38:25.800
and come looking for me.

38:25.888 --> 38:28.379
Flip side, you get to see Emma again.

38:29.266 --> 38:30.847
I'm not sure she wants to see me.

38:30.934 --> 38:32.765
You never know.

38:36.732 --> 38:39.474
When the curse is broken,
I'll send you a postcard.

38:44.239 --> 38:46.195
(MOTORCYCLE ENGINE REWING)

38:56.210 --> 38:57.700
Oh! (GASPS)

38:58.587 --> 39:00.498
I'm so sorry. Are you okay?

39:00.589 --> 39:03.422
No, it was me. I'm in a hurry.
l'm late for work.

39:03.550 --> 39:07.134
Ugh. Here, you know what,
take my scarf. It will cover up the stain.

39:10.599 --> 39:12.590
It's perfect. Thank you.

39:12.768 --> 39:14.133
-(CHUCKLES)
-Sorry.

39:16.563 --> 39:18.224
-l'm sorry.
-Thank you.

39:18.315 --> 39:20.180
l'm Tamara.

39:24.947 --> 39:25.936
Henry.

39:28.659 --> 39:29.774
We gotta talk.

39:32.621 --> 39:35.784
I'm sorry.
I'm sorry I lied to you about your dad.

39:38.085 --> 39:41.543
I promise I will never lie to you again.

39:42.256 --> 39:43.837
Just don't push me away.

39:45.634 --> 39:47.340
I won't.

40:08.240 --> 40:10.105
You ready to tell me what's going on?

40:10.200 --> 40:11.189
MARY: Yes.

40:11.285 --> 40:14.322
But before I do,
you have to promise you won't get mad.

40:14.997 --> 40:16.487
That always means good news. (SIGHS)

40:18.667 --> 40:19.827
I promise.

40:21.503 --> 40:22.663
(SIGHS)

40:23.714 --> 40:26.171
David, last week,

40:27.467 --> 40:29.594
I went to Regina's house
and confronted her.

40:29.678 --> 40:31.885
Are you out of your mind?

40:32.014 --> 40:34.005
-You promised not to get mad.
-l'm not mad!

40:34.099 --> 40:35.509
I can see that.

40:38.312 --> 40:39.802
She could've killed you.

40:39.896 --> 40:41.432
I know.

40:41.523 --> 40:43.229
That's why I went.

40:44.359 --> 40:46.065
So she would kill me.

40:48.113 --> 40:50.069
I couldn't take the guilt
over what I did to Cora.

40:50.157 --> 40:52.148
I could barely breathe.
I told her to end it.

40:52.242 --> 40:54.949
And she ripped out my heart.

40:55.078 --> 40:57.285
And when she took it out,

40:57.372 --> 40:59.454
my heart, David,

40:59.541 --> 41:02.157
it had started to blacken
because of what I did.

41:02.252 --> 41:04.163
Why didn't you tell me?

41:04.254 --> 41:08.247
Because telling you makes things real,
and I needed to believe it wasn't.

41:08.342 --> 41:11.880
That I could find a way to stop it,
that redemption was possible.

41:11.970 --> 41:13.631
Well, it is. Look at August.

41:13.722 --> 41:17.180
But it cost him everything.

41:17.351 --> 41:18.466
Oh.

41:24.399 --> 41:26.856
You are not him, Mary Margaret.

41:27.194 --> 41:29.560
And you sure as hell aren't Regina.

41:31.239 --> 41:34.652
Which means those are not
the only two options.

41:35.452 --> 41:36.988
We'll find another way. I know it.

41:37.579 --> 41:39.695
But what makes you so sure?

41:41.416 --> 41:43.122
This does.

41:44.586 --> 41:46.417
And I know it better than anyone.

41:56.473 --> 41:57.588
(BUZZING)

41:59.559 --> 42:02.346
Hey. Why haven't you called me back?
Where are you?

42:02.437 --> 42:03.722
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

42:07.234 --> 42:08.223
HER: Right here.

42:10.779 --> 42:12.610
Sorry I'm late. It's been a heck of a day.

42:12.698 --> 42:15.781
I don't have much time. Neal's in
the shower. I only have a few minutes.

42:15.909 --> 42:17.365
Then let's not waste them.
